editorialNotes.standard: We’ve played so many games that we feel like we could create our own—and now we can, all without coding classes or complex tutorials. With this ingenious educational app, it's easy to become a designer. Imagination rules as you build characters, worlds and stories for one-of-a-kind games meant to be saved, shared and—of course—played.

editorialNotes.standard: Everyone needs a task manager—and Things is adaptable enough for anyone. This Apple Design Award winner is crisp and lightweight, featuring a simple but effective interface. The ever-present Magic Plus button makes it easy to add to-do’s from anywhere in the app, and organising items is as simple as dragging them where you want them. It’s like the unicorn of productivity tools: deep enough for serious work, surprisingly easy to use, and gorgeous enough to enjoy staring at.
editorialNotes.short: Organize class projects, assignments and daily to-do lists.

editorialNotes.standard: Coloring. It’s fun, creative, and just for little kids. Right? Wrong. Each illustration is wonderful designed, and we loved switching between watercolors, colored pencils, and pens to make every piece unique.
